# Advanced Self-Improving GraphRAG Medical Research Assistant

## 1. Project Overview

### Project Title

Advanced Self-Improving GraphRAG Medical Research Assistant

### Problem Statement

Medical researchers and healthcare professionals face difficulties in:

* Searching through large volumes of medical research papers
* Connecting related medical concepts
* Identifying reliable treatment pathways
* Reducing misinformation and hallucinations from AI systems

Traditional RAG systems retrieve semantically similar text but fail to reason over relationships between diseases, symptoms, drugs, and treatments.

### Proposed Solution

Build a production-grade AI medical research assistant using:

* Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
* GraphRAG
* Hybrid Retrieval
* Knowledge Graphs
* Hallucination Detection
* Confidence Scoring
* Self-Improving Retrieval Pipelines

The system combines:

* Vector-based semantic search
* Neo4j knowledge graph reasoning
* Multi-LLM evaluation architecture

---

# 2. Objectives

## Primary Objectives

* Build an explainable medical AI assistant
* Reduce hallucinations in medical responses
* Enable graph-based medical reasoning
* Provide source-grounded medical answers
* Implement self-evaluating AI pipelines

## Secondary Objectives

* Visualize medical knowledge graphs
* Provide confidence scoring
* Build adaptive retrieval systems
* Create scalable backend architecture

